# Coding Standards

## Supabase Access

- Browser components: `import { createClient } from "@/lib/supabase/client"`
- Server components/routes: `import { createClient } from "@/lib/supabase/server"`
- Never use service_role key in client-side code
- Never expose SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY to the browser

## Data Access

- Always scope queries by `org_id` — RLS enforces this, but be explicit
- Use `.single()` for expected-one-row queries, `.maybeSingle()` when row may not exist
- For background jobs (Inngest, webhooks), use a service-role Supabase client

## Route Structure

- Auth pages: `src/app/(auth)/` — route group, no URL prefix
- Dashboard: `src/app/dashboard/` — real URL segment `/dashboard/*`
- Employee: `src/app/employee/` — real URL segment `/employee/*`
- API routes: `src/app/api/` — REST endpoints

## Components

- Use shadcn/ui for all UI primitives (Button, Card, Input, etc.)
- Mobile-first responsive design with Tailwind
- Server Components by default; add "use client" only when needed (forms, interactivity)
- Use Lucide icons via `lucide-react`

## Error Handling

- Show user-facing errors inline (not console.log)
- API routes should return proper HTTP status codes with JSON error bodies
- Wrap Supabase calls in error checks; never silently swallow errors
